    "Wies et al. [27] proposed a Probably Approximately Correct (PAC)-learning framework to formalize in-context learning, showing that with high probability, the in-context learner can PAC-learn the downstream task D, i.e.,L in-context, D -Bayes Error Rate ≤ ϵ,(9)where the Bayes Error Rate represents the theoretically lowest possible error rate for any classifier on a given task.",
