    "They established several foundational results delineating in-context learning behavior, including asymptotic optimality, monotonic error reduction with example length, and the ability to handle varying-length test examples.In-context learning enables AD systems to adapt to new scenarios without extensive retraining, crucial for handling diverse and dynamic driving environments.",
